C

Cell - Class in com.absynth.battleship.data
Class representing a cell in the BattleShipBoard.
Cell(Coord) - Constructor for class com.absynth.battleship.data.Cell
Default constructor, which takes only the absolute necessary information, the coordinates of the cell.
Cell(Coord, Cell.Content, String) - Constructor for class com.absynth.battleship.data.Cell
Constructor which initializes all the fields by calling the default constructor with the given coordinates, but also modifies the other fields based on what the user has entered in the parameters.
Cell.Content - Enum in com.absynth.battleship.data
Content which a cell can hold.
COL_CHARACTERS - Static variable in class com.absynth.battleship.data.Coord

Computer - Class in com.absynth.battleship.players
Represents a computer Player of the BattleshipBoard.
Computer(String) - Constructor for class com.absynth.battleship.players.Computer
Default constructor which takes the id which is used to identify this player.
Content() - Constructor for enum com.absynth.battleship.data.Cell.Content
 
Coord - Class in com.absynth.battleship.data
Convenient data class used to store Battleship coordinates in the form of (integer, character).
Coord(int, char) - Constructor for class com.absynth.battleship.data.Coord
Default constructor which accepts any integer as a row and any character as column but will set the row to INVALID_ROW if it is not within the range 1 - ROW_MAX and set the column to INVALID_COL if the column is not within the characters array COL_CHARACTERS.
